oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Daylight General Store
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Exterior of J. B. Henegar's General Store in Daylight. There are musicians playing a banjo and a fiddle in front of the store.
John Bell Henegar (1860-1918) was a lifelong Daylight resident. He was a popular merchant in Daylight for thirty years. He was also the postmaster for Daylight for a time.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
